00:03:19.879 --> 00:03:23.180
Death Proof

00:03:23.180 --> 00:03:27.230
Quentin Tarantino doesn't usually try to hide
the movies and characters that influence him,

00:03:27.230 --> 00:03:31.400
and Death Proof is no exception. When the
leading ladies are enjoying drinks and dancing

00:03:31.400 --> 00:03:36.709
before Kurt Russell's villain enters the picture,
he's already been introduced... sort of. It's

00:03:36.709 --> 00:03:40.719
no surprise to learn that Russell's role as
Jack Burton in Big Trouble in Little China

00:03:40.719 --> 00:03:44.961
is one of Tarantino's favorites - a fact made
clear by the hero's tanktop hanging from the

00:03:44.961 --> 00:03:48.750
bar's wall.

00:03:48.750 --> 00:03:52.290
Star Wars: Attack of The Clones

00:03:52.290 --> 00:03:56.270
The first Star Wars prequel may get some of
the harshest criticism of the series, but

00:03:56.270 --> 00:04:00.750
the tie-in video game has a lot more fans.
Star Wars: Episode 1 Racer put players behind

00:04:00.750 --> 00:04:05.780
the controls of their very own pod racer,
and they weren't alone. When Anakin and Obi-Wan

00:04:05.780 --> 00:04:10.440
head into a nightclub in Attack of the Clones,
actual footage of the game is shown - apparently,

00:04:10.440 --> 00:04:15.629
it's just as much of a spectator sport as
droid football.

00:04:15.629 --> 00:04:16.629
The LEGO Movie

00:04:16.629 --> 00:04:22.090
Most of the inside jokes and references in
The LEGO Movie make sense once viewers realize

00:04:22.090 --> 00:04:25.920
they're watching a young boy playing with
his father's carefully-constructed LEGO sets.

00:04:25.920 --> 00:04:30.260
But one joke managed to slip by plenty of
fans. When the heroes first take a trip to

00:04:30.260 --> 00:04:34.770
Cloud Cuckoo Land, the random blend of toys,
themes, and characters makes absolutely no

00:04:34.770 --> 00:04:42.190
sense whatsoever. It's never spelled out,
but when the boy's father is revealed later

00:04:42.190 --> 00:04:46.790
in the movie, he points out the LEGO and toys
his son IS allowed to play with - a box of

00:04:46.790 --> 00:04:53.590
mismatched toys in a cardboard box, complete
with a "Cloud Movers" logo.

00:04:53.590 --> 00:04:58.640
Kingsman: The Secret Service

00:04:58.640 --> 00:05:03.170
There was one sequence in this spy thriller
that no fan could ever forget, pitting star

00:05:03.170 --> 00:05:08.070
Colin Firth up against a church full of rampaging
maniacs. The actor trained for months to be

00:05:08.070 --> 00:05:12.290
able to pull off most of his own stunts, and
the frantic ballet of over the top violence

00:05:12.290 --> 00:05:17.530
is almost flawless. Until you notice the one
background actor who is less than bloodthirsty,

00:05:17.530 --> 00:05:22.560
swinging a chair so gently he's barely breaking
a sweat.&nbsp;

